{"id":14881679,"mediaExerciseId":"d9442cba-bc68-4d0f-8627-be2bdf0d9162","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":612447,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":660,"solutions":[{"id":6005530,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to calculate companyâ€™s disbursement float, collection float, and net float. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/f90a3a4b5a13e61a92f671f74897c1ae/0db4080868c382bc61bff86370a16ea9/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/f90a3a4b5a13e61a92f671f74897c1ae/0db4080868c382bc61bff86370a16ea9/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)** Notice that the disbursement float is the product of average monthly checks written and  the average number of days for the checks to clear. So, \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Disbursement float}&=\\text{Average monthly checks written}\\cdot \\text{Clearing time for the checks}\\\\\n&=\\$17,000\\cdot 4\\\\\n&=\\$68,000\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The collection float is the product of average monthly checks received and the average number of days for the checks to clear, so \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Collection float}&=\\text{Average monthly checks received}\\cdot \\text{Clearing time for the checks}\\\\\n&=(-\\$22,000)\\cdot 2\\\\\n&=-\\$44,000\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The net float is the sum of the disbursement float and the collection float. So, \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Net float}&=\\text{Disbursement float}+\\text{Collection float}\\\\\n&=\\$68,000+(-\\$44,000)\\\\\n&=\\$68,000-\\$44,000\\\\\n&=\\$24,000\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**  If the collected funds were available in one day instead of two, then the collection float will be $(-\\$22,000)\\cdot 1=-\\$22,000$. This leads to net float of  $\\$68,000-\\$22,000=\\$46,000$. \n\nTherefore, if  the cash from the payments is available to the firm after one day, then the net float will be higher.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/f90a3a4b5a13e61a92f671f74897c1ae/d465006e44e2c0136f3755c000955e46/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/f90a3a4b5a13e61a92f671f74897c1ae/d465006e44e2c0136f3755c000955e46/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"3739a581-511a-448c-9f06-5a95b8c123f6","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881680,"exerciseName":"3","page":660,"hasSolution":tr